 {"id":"franken_numpy-hi3h","title":"numpy.tril python wrapper parity","description":"Add fnp_python.tril passthrough wrapper around numpy.tril(m, k=0). Returns lower-triangular copy of m with all elements above the k-th diagonal zeroed. Include oracle test covering: square matrix k=0 (main diagonal), k=1 (one above), k=-1 (one below), rectangular matrix (3,5), 3-D batch (preserves leading axes), and dtype preservation.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T10:22:17.702705174Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T10:26:37.589828592Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T10:26:37.587163743Z","close_reason":"Completed in 30b08c5: numpy.tril wrapper with 6-scenario oracle test covering k offsets, square/rect/3-D shapes, and dtype parity","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
