+{"id":"franken_numpy-hsw8","title":"[PORT] Rust-port fnp-python raw constructors and text loaders","description":"Replace direct numpy passthroughs in crates/fnp-python/src/lib.rs for fromiter, fromstring, frombuffer, fromfile, loadtxt, and genfromtxt with Rust implementations derived from the current wrapper and parity-test spec. Success: these wrappers stop importing numpy at runtime, preserve current binary and text parsing semantics, and keep parity coverage for dtype coercion, count and offset handling, separators, comments, usecols, missing values, and error surfaces.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:44:47.279138150Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:44:47.279138150Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_numpy-hsw9","title":"[PORT] Rust-port fnp-python array creation and layout coercion family","description":"Replace direct numpy passthroughs for arange, linspace, geomspace, logspace, full, full_like, zeros_like, ones_like, empty_like, asarray, asanyarray, ascontiguousarray, asfortranarray, eye, identity, copy, require, common_type, and asarray_chkfinite with Rust implementations. Success: construction and coercion semantics are owned by fnp crates, wrappers do not import numpy, and parity tests cover dtype, layout, shape, order, and casting behavior.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_numpy-hswa","title":"[PORT] Rust-port fnp-python shape transform and padding family","description":"Replace direct numpy passthroughs for nonzero, clip, gradient, diff, roll, ravel, reshape, transpose, swapaxes, moveaxis, rollaxis, squeeze, rot90, flip, flipud, fliplr, tile, and pad with Rust implementations. Success: fnp-python dispatches into Rust shape and traversal kernels, preserves alias and order semantics, and extends parity coverage for axis handling, broadcasting, padding modes, and error surfaces.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_numpy-hswb","title":"[PORT] Rust-port fnp-python sort, set, and selection family","description":"Replace direct numpy passthroughs for histogram, histogram_bin_edges, lexsort, intersect1d, union1d, setdiff1d, isin, array_equal, array_equiv, partition, argpartition, sort, and sort_complex with Rust implementations. Success: fnp-python owns ordering, selection, and set semantics in Rust, preserves stable ordering and dtype behavior, and keeps differential parity coverage for bins, uniqueness, duplicates, kth partitioning, and comparator edge cases.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_numpy-hswc","title":"[PORT] Rust-port fnp-python statistical, NaN, and quantile reducers","description":"Replace direct numpy passthroughs for median, cov, corrcoef, nanmean, nansum, nanprod, nanmax, nanmin, nanstd, nanvar, nanargmax, nanargmin, percentile, nanpercentile, nanquantile, nanmedian, average, quantile, and allclose with Rust implementations. Success: reduction semantics move to Rust kernels, wrappers stop delegating to numpy, and conformance covers axis handling, weights, keepdims, NaN rules, interpolation methods, and numeric tolerances.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_numpy-hswd","title":"[PORT] Rust-port fnp-python scalar math, windows, and polynomial helpers","description":"Replace direct numpy passthroughs for real_if_close, angle, bartlett, hanning, hamming, blackman, heaviside, rad2deg, deg2rad, positive, negative, reciprocal, conjugate, fmod, iscomplex, isreal, isrealobj, iscomplexobj, isscalar, square, cbrt, expm1, log1p, fabs, floor_divide, real, imag, unwrap, polyder, polyint, polyadd, polysub, polymul, poly, roots, polyfit, polyval, kaiser, i0, vander, and fix with Rust implementations. Success: fnp-python exposes these helpers from Rust owned kernels, preserves dtype and domain edge cases, and extends parity tests for complex, polynomial, and windowing behavior.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_numpy-hswe","title":"[PORT] Rust-port fnp-python masked-array helper family","description":"Replace direct numpy passthroughs for ma.fix_invalid, ma.masked_where, ma.masked_equal, ma.masked_not_equal, ma.masked_inside, ma.masked_greater_equal, ma.masked_less_equal, ma.masked_outside, ma.masked_less, ma.masked_greater, ma.masked_values, ma.filled, ma.getmask, ma.getmaskarray, ma.is_masked, ma.mask_or, ma.count, ma.count_masked, ma.allequal, ma.average, ma.make_mask, ma.masked_all, ma.compressed, ma.ediff1d, ma.argmax, and ma.argmin with Rust implementations. Success: masked array semantics are owned in Rust, wrappers stop calling numpy.ma, and parity tests cover masks, fill values, axis handling, keepdims, and scalar versus ndarray returns.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_numpy-hswf","title":"[PORT] Rust-port fnp-python linear algebra surface","description":"Replace direct numpy passthroughs for linalg.matrix_rank, linalg.matrix_power, linalg.slogdet, linalg.svd, linalg.qr, linalg.cholesky, linalg.solve, linalg.eig, linalg.eigvalsh, linalg.det, linalg.tensorsolve, linalg.lstsq, linalg.vecdot, linalg.matrix_norm, linalg.matrix_transpose, linalg.svdvals, linalg.eigh, linalg.cond, linalg.norm, and linalg.multi_dot with Rust implementations. Success: fnp-linalg owns these behaviors, wrappers no longer import numpy.linalg, tuple and namedtuple surfaces are preserved, and conformance covers batched, complex, singular, and tolerance sensitive cases.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_numpy-hswg","title":"[PORT] Rust-port fnp-python FFT and tensor-product family","description":"Replace direct numpy passthroughs for fft.fft, fft.ifft, fft.fft2, fft.ifft2, fft.fftn, fft.ifftn, fft.rfftn, fft.fftshift, fft.ifftshift, tensordot, cross, inner, outer, kron, and einsum_path with Rust implementations or Rust native planning logic. Success: fnp-python owns transform and tensor-product execution in Rust, preserves axes and shape semantics, and parity tests cover odd and even lengths, complex dtypes, broadcasted tensor contractions, and planner output shape and cost reporting.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_numpy-hswh","title":"[PORT] Rust-port fnp-python structured-array and testing helper surfaces","description":"Replace direct numpy passthroughs for lib.recfunctions.drop_fields, rename_fields, append_fields, merge_arrays, unstructured_to_structured, mask_indices, and numpy.testing.assert_equal, assert_almost_equal, assert_array_almost_equal, assert_array_less, assert_approx_equal, assert_string_equal, assert_allclose, and assert_array_equal with Rust implementations. Success: fnp-python stops delegating these helper surfaces to numpy, structured dtype rewrites are implemented in Rust, assertion helpers keep current exception and message contracts, and parity tests cover both success and failure paths.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:46:55Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
